-- Alcan profit jumps on higher aluminum prices
-- 
-- Tue Oct 31, 2006 6:36am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/10/31/us-minerals-alcan-earns-idUSWEN845320061031

 

 TORONTO  (Reuters) - Third-quarter profit jumped at Alcan Inc. AL.TO ( AL.N ) on higher aluminum prices and cost controls, the company said on Tuesday. 

 Alcan, the world's second-largest maker of primary aluminum, said it earned $456 million, or $1.20 a share, up from $81 million, or 21 cents a share, a year earlier. ($1=$1.13 Canadian)